Meanwhile, from Yahoo, here 10 2010 Brazil events you probably didn't know about ! Let's have a look at them and see which have made an impact on your daily habits, jobs or habits.

. Internet taken to small towns

In April, for the first time (this year !) in history, Brazil has 100 million people connected to the internet. All major provinces have had their access expanded ! (bonus : the mobile internet access is also rising, especially among the poorer classes). For example, mobile phone access rose by 250% between 2004 and 2009. In 2010, this trend should maintain. So tell me, half of that 100 million do you represent ?

. First financial platform for NGOs

Setting up your NGO is so much easier now ! In Scond half of 2010, NGO's will be able to issue their own credit cards. This program was born out of the desire to help NGOs become more financially robust. In Brazil, there are an estimated 400 000 NGOs. And 80% of these establishments are less than 1 million dollars in turnover ! Thanks to this program, they should be able access funds more quickly and without intermediaries. Let's hope they spend it wisely !
